comments.body_markdown:
The callback function for `onCompletion` looks like

public void onCompletion(RecordMetadata metadata, Exception e) {
    if (e != null)
      log.debug(&quot;Send failed for record {}&quot;, record, e);
  }

So if the exception is thrown the variable `e` will be non null. Thus you will be able to understand whether the async callback threw an exception or not.

